<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="23.[96,516,1318,1562]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Known only from the summit of Mt. Lindesay, males can be identified by a white &quot;crown&quot; at the top of a triangular fan. In one display both legs III are waved as the fan is rotated from side to side. In a second display the fan is twisted to one side and a single leg is kicked.</paragraph>
